args:
Today's Observer: Mitsuba

We all know Pipple wants to be
eaten, but he took it to another level
today!
Right! Time for me to make some stock!
Hmm... I think I'm craving veggies today.\nFirst, I'll fill the pot with water—
Pipple! In this house, we do NOT bring\nourselves to a boil over low heat!
Stop trying to get me to cook you.\nMy cookware is for non-sentient\ningredients only!
Have we not been over this several times?
Hey, you two. Why all the commotion?
Oh, just the usual—Pipple clamoring for\ndeath's steamy, bubbling-hot embrace.
Stop causing trouble for people, Pipple.\nI grow tired of repeating this to you.
Er, why is he bringing us a bunch of\nvegetables?
Maybe he decided to cool it after you\ngot mad at him, so now he's trying\nto help out instead?
Well, no complaints here! I was just\nthinking that I'd like to perfect my\nvegetable stock recipe today.
Thanks, little guy! I'll make good use\nof your gift! Hand them here.
Huh? You're NOT giving them to us?\nThen why're you hoarding so many?
He didn't bring those vegetables over to\nhelp us.
He's taken them hostage—and he won't\ngive them back unless we eat him.

This shocking act marked the start
of the great Vegetable War. Without
vegetables, how were we supposed
to make healthy, nourishing meals?
This is quite the pickle...\nEr, maybe that was a poor choice of words.
He has all the castle's vegetables\nin his clutches—and if we don't meet\nhis demands, he won't give them back.
Here's an idea—let's just go buy more.
I think that's gonna be a no-go, bud.
Even if we could, we had so many\nvegetables that replacing them all\nwould drain the treasury dry.
But that means we'd have to eat HIM.\nDoes anyone here have the guts to do it?
The stalemate between man and vegetable\ncontinued for several days more...
Urgh... I need some veggies already!\nOr at least vegetable STOCK!
Same. Let's just say my guts ain't happy.
I think that's just because you've been\neating too much in general.
You're not wrong that we're all missing\nveggies in our diets, though.
We really need to do something...\nBut is eating Pipple our only option?
Wait, I have a plan! Leave this to me!
Please don't tell me you're going to—
Glad you could make it, Pipple!\nIt's time to grant your wish.\nHop in my pot!
Heh. Did I get your hopes up?\nI actually just want to extract some\nof your nutrients for my stock.
I know that's not exactly what you want,\nbut we'd still be ＂eating＂ you, in a sense.\nIs that a fair compromise?
I'm sorry. I know you're disappointed.
But believe me when I say we're not trying\nto upset you or disregard your feelings.
No matter who or what you are,\nyou're our irreplaceable friend.
Can't we meet halfway and make up?\nPlease?
Does that mean you'll forgive me, Pipple?
Excellent. Then let's get this\nPipple stock percolating!
He looks like he enjoyed that.
I boiled the water niiice and slow,\nkeeping an eye on the temperature.
Don't worry. I haven't forgotten\nmy promise.
Holy smokes! It's actually REALLY GOOD!
...Mmm. You're right. It has a mild,\nherbaceous flavor. Very mellow.

And so the great Vegetable War
came to a shocking conclusion.
Even the most soup-averse among us
came 'round after a savory sip of Pip.
